nodes.body: Should I rename the structure `Module.Core` to `Module.MinimalAxioms`?  Or just get rid of it, to be consistent with the other `ofMinimalAxioms` functions?

> Or just get rid of it, to be consistent with the other `ofMinimalAxioms` functions?

This sounds like a good idea to me. The original design is vestigial from the refactor in https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/pull/456, so I don't think we need to be attached to it.

> Can you update the PR title to reflect the [commit conventions](https://leanprover-community.github.io/contribute/commit.html)?

Sure!  Should that be added to [How to contribute to mathlib](https://leanprover-community.github.io/contribute/index.html), in the bullet that mentions `git commit -a`?
@eric-wieser I believe I've addressed all your comments.  Please let me know if you'd like me to change anything else before merging.  And thanks for reviewing and your helpful comments!

bors merge

Thanks!

LGTM, thanks!

Can you update the PR title to reflect the [commit conventions](https://leanprover-community.github.io/contribute/commit.html)?

```suggestion
# Minimal Axioms for a Module
```

```suggestion
`AddCommGroup`, while proving a minimum number of equalities.
```

```suggestion
abbrev Module.ofMinimalAxioms {R : Type u} {M : Type v} [Semiring R] [AddCommGroup M] [SMul R M]
```
which I think is what the other `ofMinimalAxioms` do
The other ones all use `def`.
`Subspace` uses `abbrev`, perhaps that's what you're thinking of?

`@[reducible] def` means the same thing as `abbrev` :)

https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/796fc3fcc37bab117a8a54537a43311289765e67/Mathlib/Algebra/Field/MinimalAxioms.lean#L27-L28
Using `reducible` instead for consistency is also fine.

```suggestion
@[reducible]
def Module.ofMinimalAxioms {R : Type u} {M : Type v} [Semiring R] [AddCommGroup M] [SMul R M]
```
